# Frontend design — minimal by default

When working on the Angular client (`Client/`):

## Do not add design or styling unless I explicitly ask

- Do **not** write or edit CSS/SCSS (component styles, `styles.scss`, layout, colors, spacing, typography, animations, responsive breakpoints).
- Do **not** add inline `style` attributes or styling-oriented utility classes for visual polish.
- Do **not** introduce UI/design libraries (e.g. Tailwind, Bootstrap, Angular Material) unless I request them.
- Do **not** “improve”, “polish”, or “make it look nice” on your own.

## Only add what I ask for

- Implement the **specific feature, logic, route, service, or markup** I requested — nothing extra.
- HTML should be **minimal and functional** (structure needed for the feature to work), not a designed UI.
- If styling is required for the feature to function (e.g. hiding an element), prefer the smallest possible change and only when necessary — otherwise skip styling and tell me if design is needed.

## When I do ask for design

- Follow my instructions exactly; do not expand scope beyond what I described.
